title: [CRASH] - Unknown issues with Redis Sentinel & RedisTimeSeries
body:
Hi, 

I am encountering this crash with one of our Redis nodes that use RedisTimeSeries (1.4.9). One node is primary and the other is a replica. We use HAProxy to load balance READs and Redis Sentinel to handle failovers.

I ran: `redis-server --test-memory 4096` and the result was good.

Distribution

```
LSB Version:	:core-4.1-amd64:core-4.1-noarch
Distributor ID:	Amazon
Description:	Amazon Linux release 2 (Karoo)
Release:	2
Codename:	Karoo
```

Below is a report from the 2nd crash. We got the primary and replica back up and running and it went down again ~30 min later

